# Code Style Rules

## Naming

- Use `camelCase` for variables, functions, and object properties
- Use `PascalCase` for React components, classes, and types
- Use descriptive names that explain purpose
- Avoid single-letter variables except for short, obvious cases like loop indices

## File Structure

- Keep files focused on one responsibility
- Group related logic together
- Prefer small helper functions over long inline blocks
- Use clear section ordering: imports, constants, main logic, exports

## Formatting

- Keep formatting consistent with the existing file
- Prefer readable line breaks over dense one-line expressions
- Use whitespace to separate logical sections
- Avoid unnecessary comments; add brief comments only when intent is not obvious

## Examples

```ts
// Avoid
const x = getDiscountedCashFlow(data);

// Prefer
const discountedCashFlow = getDiscountedCashFlow(data);
```

```ts
// Avoid
function calc(v: number) {
  return v * 1.1;
}

// Prefer
function calculateGrowthRate(baseValue: number) {
  return baseValue * 1.1;
}
```
